    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Haider In Their Future</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steven Lucks letter on Roger Cohen's April 30 article holds placing sanctions against Austran goverment for fascist remarks made by Jorg Haider is undemocratic</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Haider's coalition came to power by popular vote in a democratic institution. Likewise, the coalition can be removed from power if so desired by the electorate. This is a key element of democracy. By placing sanctions against the Austrian government for fascist remarks made by Haider, rather than for undemocratic policies implemented by the government, the European Union has infringed on Austria's national sovereignty.</p>
        <p>Steven Lucks</p>
        <p>Princeton, N.J.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
